# My GitHub Pages Site

This repository will be used to host a static website using GitHub Pages.

## Branches
- `main`: Source code or project files
- `gh-pages`: Deployed website content (GitHub Pages)

## Getting Started

To publish your site:
1. Create a `gh-pages` branch
2. Add static HTML/CSS/JS content (e.g., `index.html`)
3. Go to **Settings > Pages**, and set the source to `gh-pages` branch

Happy building!
